The paper discusses the use of analog arrays for deep learning, which falls under the category of hardware implementations for neural networks (cs.ET). The focus is on convolutional neural networks (ConvNets) and their efficient implementation on analog arrays, which relates to computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of multiple kernel matrices for parallel training, which relates to neural network optimization (cs.NE) and control systems (cs.SY).
